having jaunty-proposed enabled is a very very very bad idea.
also, your medibuntu line says "feisty" rather than "jaunty" as it should
remove jaunty-proposed, fix medibuntu, save, and then "sudo apt-get update". then try again installing bind9
it may not be fixable easily, however, depending on what got installed from -proposed
where it says "feisty", change that to "jaunty"
have you also typed "sudo apt-get update"?
output of "apt-cache policy libbind9-40 ; apt-cache policy bind9" please?
